main event: A UFO was observed hovering and exhibiting highly illuminated characteristics near Cora, Wyoming on October 9, 1962.
interesting points: The UFO remained semi-stationary for over 15 minutes at an altitude of approximately 12,000 feet., Another brighter object was observed shortly after the first and hovered at about 20,000 feet., The first object was reported to discharge some kind of material., The observation occurred near the G. P. Ranch on Green River Lake., Witnesses described the objects to have no sound and to be brighter than conventional aircraft.
witness description: Observers were inhabitants of Cora and a nearby ranch; details of their ages and backgrounds were included, indicating they were stable individuals.
